<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="575" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,690,1363]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,690,715]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[306,429,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">Coloration</emphasis>
. Body yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[723,789,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[287,1303,217,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[268,1318,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hephathus freyi A, Body, dorsal view; B, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; C, Face. Hephathus dilatatus sp. nov. D, Body, dorsal view; E, Body, lateral view; F, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; G, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240614/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
Fig. 
<number box="[778,789,691,715]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Face with four black spots on upper part, two black discoidal spots extending from middle to clypellus (
<figureCitation box="[730,793,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[287,1303,217,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[268,1318,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hephathus freyi A, Body, dorsal view; B, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; C, Face. Hephathus dilatatus sp. nov. D, Body, dorsal view; E, Body, lateral view; F, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; G, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240614/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
Fig. 
<number box="[782,793,727,751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
G). Pronotum brown with two black spots on fore margin behind eyes. Scutellum yellowish with black triangular spots in side angles (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1070,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[287,1303,217,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[268,1318,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hephathus freyi A, Body, dorsal view; B, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; C, Face. Hephathus dilatatus sp. nov. D, Body, dorsal view; E, Body, lateral view; F, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; G, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240614/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
Fig. 
<number box="[1059,1070,763,787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,690,1363]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis box="[199,336,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">Morphology</emphasis>
. Body form typically wedge-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[785,854,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[287,1303,217,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[268,1318,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hephathus freyi A, Body, dorsal view; B, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; C, Face. Hephathus dilatatus sp. nov. D, Body, dorsal view; E, Body, lateral view; F, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; G, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240614/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
Fig. 
<number box="[843,854,799,823]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Head wider than pronotum, crown shorter in middle than next to eyes. Pronotum broad, slightly concave on posterior margin, striae on surface dense, oblique. Mesonotum triangular, with one heavy notch on posterior region (
<figureCitation box="[919,986,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[287,1303,217,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[268,1318,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hephathus freyi A, Body, dorsal view; B, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; C, Face. Hephathus dilatatus sp. nov. D, Body, dorsal view; E, Body, lateral view; F, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; G, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240614/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
Fig. 
<number box="[975,986,871,895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F). Face across eyes longer than wide, ocelli on face, between eyes with their distance about 4.0 times than that of ocellus to adjacent eye, clypellus oblong (
<figureCitation box="[244,307,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[287,1303,217,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[268,1318,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hephathus freyi A, Body, dorsal view; B, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; C, Face. Hephathus dilatatus sp. nov. D, Body, dorsal view; E, Body, lateral view; F, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; G, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240614/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
Fig. 
<number box="[296,307,943,967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
G). Forewing has 
<number box="[512,526,943,967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="3.0">3</number>
anteapical cells (
<figureCitation box="[721,784,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[287,1303,217,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[268,1318,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hephathus freyi A, Body, dorsal view; B, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; C, Face. Hephathus dilatatus sp. nov. D, Body, dorsal view; E, Body, lateral view; F, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; G, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240614/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
Fig. 
<number box="[773,784,943,967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
E). 
<collectingCountry box="[827,883,942,967]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibial chaetotaxy PD 
<number box="[1123,1150,943,967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="10.0">10</number>
, AD 
<number box="[1205,1218,943,967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="7.0">7</number>
, AV 
<number box="[1272,1284,942,967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="5.0">5</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,690,1363]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis box="[199,363,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer nearly triangular, subgenital plates long with marginal setae (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1225,978,1003]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[203,1339,201,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[184,1381,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hephathus dilatatus A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Aedeagus, caudal view; C, Aedeagus, lateral view; D, Connective, ventral view; E, Connective, lateral view; F, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240616/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
Fig. 
<number box="[1211,1225,979,1003]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Aedeagal shaft long, upturned dorsally; with parallel lateral margins and rounded apex in caudal view; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation box="[1326,1401,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[203,1339,201,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[184,1381,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hephathus dilatatus A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Aedeagus, caudal view; C, Aedeagus, lateral view; D, Connective, ventral view; E, Connective, lateral view; F, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240616/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
Figs. 
<number box="[1389,1401,1015,1039]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B– C). Connective with a fingerlike protrusion in middle between arms, both lateral arms bent dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1367,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[203,1339,201,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[184,1381,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hephathus dilatatus A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Aedeagus, caudal view; C, Aedeagus, lateral view; D, Connective, ventral view; E, Connective, lateral view; F, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240616/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
Figs. 
<number box="[1354,1367,1051,1075]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
D–E). Style slender, slightly dorsally curved, with blunt tips (
<figureCitation box="[764,830,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[203,1339,201,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[184,1381,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hephathus dilatatus A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Aedeagus, caudal view; C, Aedeagus, lateral view; D, Connective, ventral view; E, Connective, lateral view; F, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240616/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
Fig. 
<number box="[816,830,1087,1111]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,690,1363]" box="[199,641,1122,1147]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,363,1122,1147]" pageId="6" pageNumber="575">Measurement</emphasis>
